text: Anu is the Mesopotamian god of the sky. The Sumerians describe him as the embodiment of the sky which can come to Earth in human form. Anu is also the King of Gods, and sometimes said to create humans with the assistance of his sons Enlil and/or Enki Anu is not talked about in the Hebrew scriptures. == References == Category:Mesopotamia Category:Gods and goddesses of the sky
